# unexpected blockers encountered (resolved or flagged)

@blocker_observed_1 ubu1/ubu2/hetzner hexa_real runtime requires HEXA_LANG env to load `self/stdlib/ai_err.hexa` — without it, resource_lint.hexa errors "undefined function: ai_err_exit". Resolution: switched _resolve_child_bin to direct awk parse of .resource (no hexa-runtime dependency).
@blocker_observed_2 hive-exec wrapper (~/.hx/bin/hive-exec) hardcoded /Users/ghost/core/hive — fixed by adding $HOME/core/hive generic fallback BEFORE the Mac literal. Now usable on every host whose hive checkout sits at $HOME/core/hive.
@blocker_observed_3 hetzner hexa runtime emits stderr "security warning: exec() argument contains shell metacharacters" for awk patterns, but output integrity is preserved. Non-fatal cosmetic noise — flagged for separate hexa-runtime sandboxing review.
@blocker_observed_4 ubu1 has no ~/.hx/bin/nexus shim (only ubu2 + hetzner do). `nexus kick tree` invoked via direct hexa_real run path on ubu1. Shim install flagged for separate task (out of sub-L scope).
@blocker_observed_5 hetzner /root/.hx/packages/nexus/tool/ missing kick_tree.hexa (sub-I prior sync gap). Repo-path tree works fine; only the package mirror needs one more rsync pass — flagged.

